This paper is primarily focused on image denoising using convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of wider CNNs with larger reception fields and more channels, which is a technique commonly used in deep learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the ability of CNNs to learn pixel-distribution, which is a concept related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of wider CNNs also involves the optimization of network architecture, which is a topic in neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed method using quantitative and visual evaluations, which is a common practice in multimedia (cs.MM) research.
